Memoization is remembering something after you did it once the slow way. When you ask me "What's the 24th Fibonacci number?" I have to go calculate it, but I remember the answer so the second time you ask me, I can say it right away. And one more important point is that the loss functions usually should be differentiable, which is not the case for most of metric functions used.
